By Shifting the points¶

In [39]:
## Change the coordinates by a little so that it is inside SF
def shift(pt):
    value = pt.coords[0]
    ## if south of sf move north/east a little
    if(value[1] < 37.75):
        value = (value[0] + 0.001, value[1] + 0.001)
    ## the rest shift south/east a little
    else:
        ## right side of SF
        if(value[0] > -122.425):
            ## move a little north/west
            value = (value[0] - 0.002, value[1] - 0.0005)
        else:
            value = (value[0] + 0.002, value[1] - 0.0005)
    return Point(value)

df_failed['geometry'] = df_failed['geometry'].apply(shift)

In [51]:
## dataframe counting tickets per block
df_vio = pd.DataFrame()
for name, idx in zip(['Half1', 'Half2', 'Weekend'], 
                     [half1, half2, weekend]):
    ## Count number of tickets per violation group
    tmp = df_block[idx].groupby(['blockid', 'violation_group']).size().unstack().fillna(value=0)
    ## count total number of tickets per block
    tmp['counts'] = tmp.sum(axis=1)
    tmp.reset_index(inplace=True)
    ## Average number of tickets per block per day
    tmp['tick_avg'] = tmp.counts/df_block.date[idx].unique().shape[0]
    print('{} shape before merge: {}'.format(name, tmp.shape))
    
    ## merge result to block shapefile to get all blocks
    tmp = pd.merge(block, tmp, on='blockid', how='left')
    tmp.fillna(value=0, inplace=True)
    
    ## Add season's name
    tmp['season'] = name
    ## append to master dataframe
    df_vio = df_vio.append(tmp, ignore_index=True)

del tmp, name, idx, half1, half2

Summary Function¶

In [57]:
## Produce a violin plots on ticket average
def sum_violin(df, season, avg):
    """
    Parameters
    ----------
    df : dataframe
    season: str
    avg: float or integer
    """
    idx = df.season.isin([season])
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2, figsize=(12,3))
    sns.violinplot(x=df.loc[idx, 'tick_avg'], ax=axs[0])
    axs[0].set_title(season + ': Daily Tickets Average', 
                     fontsize=12)
    sns.violinplot(x=df.loc[idx, 'tick_avg'], ax=axs[1])
    axs[1].set_xlim(0, avg)
    axs[1].set_title('Under ' + str(avg) + ' Tickets Average', 
                 fontsize=12)
    plt.show()
In [58]:
## Produces a choropleth map on average ticket above a certain amount 
def sum_map(df, season, avg, df_map):
    """
    Parameters
    ----------
    df : geopandas dataframe
    season: str 
        season of interest
    avg: float or integer
        the average ticket to filter
    df_map: geopandas dataframe
        base map 
    """
    idx = df.season.isin([season])
    
    print('Blocks < ' + str(avg) + ' tickets average: {:,}'\
      .format((df.loc[idx, 'tick_avg'] <= avg).sum()))
    print('Blocks >= ' + str(avg) + ' tickets average: {:,}'\
      .format((df.loc[idx, 'tick_avg'] > avg).sum()))
    
    base = df_map.plot(color='white', 
                  edgecolor='black',
                  linewidth=0.3,
                  figsize=(12, 12))
    df[idx & (df.tick_avg >= avg)].plot(edgecolor='black',
                                        linewidth=.5,
                                        column='tick_avg', 
                                        scheme='QUANTILES',
                                        k=9,
                                        legend=True,
                                        ax=base)
    plt.ylim(37.70, 37.82)
    plt.xlim(-122.52, -122.34)
    plt.title(season + ': Ticket Daily Average >= ' + str(avg),
              fontsize=20)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

AZTool Result¶

In [67]:
def result_check(path, folder, season, df):
    """
    Parameters
    ----------
    path : str
        path location to folder
    folder: str
        where all the files are at
    season: str
        season of interest
    df: geopandas dataframe
        dataframe used in AZTool
    """
    ## Filepath to aztool results
    fp = os.path.join(path, folder)
    
    ## Make sure that AZM_ID is the same as blockid
    ## because pat files are made from AZTImporter
    pat = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(fp, season.lower() + '.pat'))
    ## drop the last row which is created from AZTImporter
    pat.drop(index=pat.shape[0]-1, inplace=True)
    assert (pat.AZM_ID == pat.blockid).all(), season + ': AZM_ID does not match with blockid'
    
    ## print out training time
    with open(os.path.join(fp, season.lower() + '_output.log'), 'r') as f:
        print(list(f)[-1])
    
    ## Read output from AZTool
    output = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(fp, season.lower() + '_output.csv'), dtype=object)
    
    ## Number of regions produced
    print('Number of regions: {}'.format(output.TractID.unique().shape[0]))
    
    ## Merge
    region = pd.merge(df[df.season.isin([season])], 
                      output, 
                      how='left', 
                      left_on='blockid', 
                      right_on='BldBlID')
    
    ## dissolve blocks into one whole region
    region = region.dissolve(by='TractID', aggfunc='sum')
    region.reset_index(inplace=True)
    ## round tick_avg for easier visualization
    region['tick_avg'] = region.tick_avg.round().astype(int)
    
    ## Plot regional average
    region.tick_avg.plot.hist()
    plt.title('Distribution of Daily Average Tickets per Region')
    plt.xlabel('Daily Avg Tickets')
    plt.show()

    if region.tick_avg.unique().shape[0] == 1:
        kwds = {}
    else:
        kwds = dict(legend_kwds = {'title': 'Daily Avg'},
                    scheme = 'Fisher_Jenks',
                    cmap='Accent',
                    legend=True)
        
    
    ## Plot region on map
    region.plot(column='tick_avg',
                edgecolor='black',
                figsize=(10,8),
                **kwds)
    plt.axis('equal')
    plt.title(season, fontsize=16)
    plt.show()
    
    # return the merge dataframe
    return region
In [68]:
def region_prop(df):
    """
    Convert violation for each region to proportion 
    
    Parameters
    ----------
    df : geopandas dataframe
    """
    cols = ['Color Curb', 'Commerical', 'Handicap Related', 'Illegal Parking', 
            'License Plate', 'Meter Related', 'No Parking', 'Other', 
            'Overtime', 'Safety', 'Traffic Related', 'Transit Related',]
    for col in cols:
        df[col] = df[col]/df['counts']
